# PacketcraftR 0.2.0-beta.1

Source commit: `{{SOURCE_COMMIT}}`

Workspace archive SHA-256: `{{ARCHIVE_SHA256}}`

Post-publication portable artifact smoke evidence: {{SMOKE_EVIDENCE}}

This beta is the v0.2 compatibility-freeze checkpoint. The public Rust façade,
14-command CLI grammar and exit classes, packet/output schemas, exact portable
wire behavior, fixtures, and GitHub Release artifact contract are frozen.

## Distribution

GitHub Releases are the only distribution channel. The attached
`packetcraftr-workspace-0.2.0-beta.1.tar.gz` is a complete buildable workspace;
`SHA256SUMS` authenticates it. The archive's `RELEASE-METADATA.toml` binds the
version and tag to the source commit above. All five Cargo packages retain
`publish = false`; nothing is published to crates.io or another registry.

The MSRV is Rust 1.96.0. Install the portable CLI from the verified extracted
workspace with:

```console
cargo install --locked --path . --no-default-features
packetcraftr --version
```

## Frozen baselines

- Public Rust API: `319ac1647b8e40e9453178e418c40a26bfab98914df425b6e2c7dab1b8941762`
- CLI/schema: `{{CLI_SCHEMA_BASELINE}}`

## Qualification status

The portable default/no-default/all-feature build and test profiles are green
on hosted Linux, macOS, and Windows CI. Stable-promised native implementations
are present, but privileged Linux live-I/O, macOS arm64/x86_64 live-I/O,
Windows x86_64 MSVC + Npcap live-I/O, cross-platform parity, and the final
security/resource/package audit remain RC qualification gates.

See the [platform matrix](https://github.com/tyk-swe/pcr/blob/v0.2.0-beta.1/docs/platform-support.md),
[installation guide](https://github.com/tyk-swe/pcr/blob/v0.2.0-beta.1/docs/install-and-release.md),
and [beta feedback policy](https://github.com/tyk-swe/pcr/blob/v0.2.0-beta.1/docs/beta-feedback.md).
Confirmed freeze regressions are 0.2.0 release blockers before RC.
